Yes, you should retry when `AtomicInteger.compareAndSet()` fails. This method is part of the Compare-And-Swap (CAS) pattern, which is used for lock-free concurrency control. 

When `compareAndSet(current, next)` returns false, it indicates that another thread has modified the value since you last read it. You should update your `current` value by calling `atomic.get()` again and retry the CAS operation. 

Here’s a concise implementation:

```java
