To implement a retry mechanism using `Supplier<T>`, you can follow this structure:

```java
import java.util.function.Supplier;

public class RetryUtil {

    public static <T> T retry(Supplier<T> supplier, int maxRetries) {
        int attempts = 0;
        while (attempts < maxRetries) {
            try {
                return supplier.get();
            } catch (Exception e) {
                attempts++;
                if (attempts >= maxRetries) {
                    throw e; // Rethrow after max retries
                }
            }
        }
        throw new RuntimeException("Max retries exceeded");
    }
}
```

### Key Points:
- Wrap the operation in a `Supplier<T>`.
- Use a loop to retry up to `maxRetries`.
- Catch exceptions and re-invoke `supplier.get()` on failure.
- Rethrow the exception after exceeding the retry limit.

