To create a custom health indicator in Spring Boot, implement the `HealthIndicator` interface and override the `health()` method. This method should return a `Health` object indicating the health status. Use `Health.up()` for a healthy state and `Health.down()` with details for an unhealthy state. Ensure your custom indicator is a Spring bean to be auto-registered.

Example:

```java
import org.springframework.boot.actuate.health.Health;
import org.springframework.boot.actuate.health.HealthIndicator;
import org.springframework.stereotype.Component;

@Component
public class CustomHealthIndicator implements HealthIndicator {

    @Override
    public Health health() {
        // Perform health check logic
        boolean isHealthy = checkHealth();

        if (isHealthy) {
            return Health.up().build();
        } else {
            return Health.down().withDetail("Error", "Service is down").build();
        }
    }

