In Angular 17+, a child component can notify the parent of internal signal changes using the `output()` decorator with a signal. Here's how to implement it:

1. **Child Component**: Define an `Output` property and emit the signal.

```typescript
import { Component, Output, EventEmitter } from '@angular/core';
import { signal } from '@angular/core';

@Component({
  selector: 'child-component',
  template: `<button (click)="changeSignal()">Change Signal</button>`
})
export class ChildComponent {
  private childSignal = signal(false);
  @Output() signalChanged = new EventEmitter<boolean>();

  changeSignal() {
    this.childSignal.set(!this.childSignal());
    this.signalChanged.emit(this.childSignal());
  }
}
