A Selector in NgRx is a pure function that selects a slice of state from the store. It can derive state by transforming or combining existing state properties. 

Memoization is crucial because it caches the results of selectors. A memoized selector recalculates its output only when its input state changes, thus preventing unnecessary re-renders in components. This improves performance by reducing computational overhead. 

Selectors can also be composed, allowing for more complex state derivations while maintaining efficiency through memoization. 

Example:
```typescript
import { createSelector } from '@ngrx/store';

