        .maxMessagesPerPoll(5)
        .pollTimeout(Duration.ofSeconds(5))
        .build());
    return factory;
}
```

To configure AWS SDK v2 clients as Spring Beans in Spring Boot, you can define a method annotated with `@Bean`. This method will create and return the desired AWS client, such as `S3Client`. You can also inject an `AwsCredentialsProvider` bean to manage credentials.

